<p>Symptoms According to Standard Theory</p>
<h1>DSM Symptoms According to The Standard Theory of Psychology</h1>
<p>The following list outlines the primary symptoms in the DSM.<br />Each symptom is labelled according to the related category<br />of The Standard Theory of Psychology preliminarily as follows:</p>
<p>Irregular Impulse - components of impulse, subtraction, or compression</p>
<p>Intimacy Dysfunction - 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6</p>
<p>Social Identity Disorder - 9, 8, 7, 17, 27, 54, 117, gapping</p>
<p>Irregular Impulse - metaphysical, impulsive, compulsive, compulsive impulse</p>
<p>Memory-based (delusion) - cyclic</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>MOOD &amp; EMOTIONAL EXPERIENCE</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Persistent sadness or low mood - 2<br />- Reduced interest or pleasure - 3<br />- Elevated or expansive mood - 2<br />- Irritability - 2<br />- Emotional numbness - 17<br />- Excessive guilt or shame - 17<br />- Hopelessness - 17<br />- Rapid mood changes - 2<br />- Excessive worry - 17<br />- Disproportionate fear - 2/gapping<br />- Sudden panic or fear surges - 2/gapping<br />- Emotional detachment - 17<br />- Difficulty experiencing positive emotions - 17</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>THOUGHT CONTENT &amp; PERCEPTION</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Intrusive or unwanted thoughts - 1<br />- Obsessions - 3<br />- Compulsions - 3<br />- Persistent doubts - 3<br />- Rumination - 3<br />- Catastrophic thinking - 1<br />- Delusional beliefs - 1/cyclic<br />- Grandiosity - 1<br />- Paranoia or suspicious thinking - 1<br />- Thought blocking - 1<br />- Hallucinations (any sensory type) - 1<br />- Distorted reality perception - 1<br />- Magical or irrational beliefs - 1<br />- Suicidal thoughts - 1<br />- Preoccupation with death - 1</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>COGNITIVE FUNCTIONING</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Concentration difficulties - 3<br />- Impaired attention - 3<br />- Memory problems - 2, cyclic<br />- Mental confusion - 3<br />- Disorganized thinking - 1, 3<br />- Racing thoughts - 3<br />- Slowed thinking - 1<br />- Poor decision-making - 3<br />- Cognitive rigidity - 3</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>BEHAVIOR &amp; ACTIVITY</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Psychomotor agitation - component of impulse<br />- Psychomotor slowing - component of impulse<br />- Impulsivity - impulsive communication<br />- Risk-taking behavior - compulsive communication<br />- Avoidance behaviors - 3<br />- Social withdrawal - 3<br />- Repetitive behaviors - 3<br />- Ritualistic actions - 3<br />- Aggression - 2<br />- Self-injury - 1<br />- Substance use behaviors - impulsive<br />- Loss of behavioral control - impulsive<br />- Excessive reassurance seeking - 17</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>SLEEP &amp; ENERGY</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>- Difficulty sleeping - 2<br />- Excessive sleeping - 2<br />- Restless sleep - 2<br />- Reduced need for sleep - 2<br />- Fatigue - 2<br />- Low energy - 2<br />- Physical restlessness - 2</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>APPETITE &amp; WEIGHT</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Increased appetite - 2<br />- Decreased appetite - 2<br />- Weight gain - 2<br />- Weight loss - 2<br />- Restrictive eating - 2<br />- Binge eating - 2<br />- Purging behaviors - 2</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>ANXIETY &amp; STRESS RESPONSES</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Heightened stress response - 3<br />- Inability to relax - 3<br />- Hypervigilance - 3<br />- Exaggerated startle response - Gap<br />- Avoidance of reminders - 17<br />- Re-experiencing distress - 3<br />- Dissociation - 1<br />- Emotional reactivity to stress - Impulsive</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>IDENTITY &amp; SELF-EXPERIENCE</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Identity disturbance - 1, 5<br />- Unstable self-image - 1, 5<br />- Chronic emptiness - 1<br />- Depersonalization - 1<br />- Derealization - 1<br />- Dependence on others for decisions - 17</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>INTERPERSONAL FUNCTIONING</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Fear of abandonment - 17<br />- Relationship instability - 17<br />- Social anxiety - 5<br />- Distrust of others - 1<br />- Interpersonal sensitivity - 3<br />- Boundary instability - 4<br />- Frequent interpersonal conflict - 3, impulsive</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>SPEECH &amp; COMMUNICATION</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Pressured speech - 3<br />- Rapid speech - 3<br />- Reduced speech output - 3<br />- Monotone speech - 3<br />- Circumstantial speech - 27<br />- Tangential speech - 27<br />- Incoherent speech - 3</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>MOTIVATION &amp; GOAL-DIRECTED ACTIVITY</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Reduced motivation - 3<br />- Lack of initiative - 3<br />- Difficulty completing tasks - 3<br />- Excessive goal-directed activity - 3<br />- Difficulty sustaining effort - 3</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>PHYSICAL &amp; SOMATIC EXPERIENCES</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Unexplained physical symptoms - 2<br />- Stress-related pain - 2<br />- Gastrointestinal distress linked to stress - 2<br />- Muscle tension - 2<br />- Preoccupation with bodily symptoms - 2</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>SEXUAL &amp; INTIMATE FUNCTIONING</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Reduced sexual interest - metaphysical<br />- Increased sexual drive - 2<br />- Sexual risk-taking - compulsive<br />- Sexual functioning distress - metaphysical</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>INSIGHT &amp; SELF-AWARENESS</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Limited insight - 1, 7<br />- Denial of difficulties - 5<br />- Externalization of blame - 3, 17<br />- Over-identification with symptoms - 7, 8</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>DEVELOPMENTAL &amp; ADAPTIVE FUNCTIONING</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------<br />- Difficulty adapting to change - 3<br />- Repetitive interests or behaviors - 3<br />- Sensory sensitivity - 2<br />- Emotional regulation difficulties - 17</p>
<p>--------------------------------------------------</p>
